      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's weird when you put it that way. like, you're saying that fighting the emptiness is actually the thing making it so hard to breathe. so if the darkness is the only thing that's real... why does everyone act like trying to escape it is the only way to live? why isn't just accepting the end an option?",
